The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.    South Africa â€™s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index advanced for
a second day, adding 106.14, or 0.4 percent, to 30,718.55 at the
5 p.m. close of trading in Johannesburg.    Accentuate Ltd. (ACE)  : The maker of cleaning products
reports first-half earnings. The shares dropped 6 cents, or 9.1
percent, to 60 cents.    Adcock Ingram Holdings Ltd. (AIP)  : The drugs supplier
plans to more than double liquids production as part of a 1.5
billion-rand ($212.3 million) expansion,  Business Report  said,
citing Chief Executive Officer Jonathan Louw. Shares in the
company were little changed at 54.51 rand.    Basil Read Holdings Ltd. (BSR)  : The construction and
engineering company reports annual earnings. Its shares declined
13 cents, or 1.2 percent, to 10.40 rand.  BioSience Brands Ltd. (BIO SJ): The health and nutritional
products supplier said its loss widened to 10.1 million rand in
the six months through Dec. 31 from 1.4 million rand a year
earlier. Shares in the company were unchanged at 1 cent.  Morvest Business Group Ltd. (MOR SJ): The computer-services
company agreed to buy 50 percent of R&S Consulting for 60
million rand. The shares were unchanged at 19 cents.    Pinnacle Technology Holdings Ltd. (PNC)  : The computer
and networking group said net income for the six months through
December jumped 61 percent to 89 million rand. The stock rose 5
cents, or 0.7 percent, to 7.15 rand.  Village Main Reef Ltd. (VIL SJ): The platinum miner is
scheduled to report first-half earnings. Shares in the company
declined 1 cent, to 0.5 percent, to 1.99 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) gained 2.6 percent to $24.07.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) rose 0.6 percent to $44.04. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) increased 3.9 percent to $73.25. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) jumped 6.3 percent to $4.75. Gold Fields Ltd.
(GFI US) fell 0.3 percent to $16.38. Harmony Gold Mining Co.
(HMY US) fell 1.2 percent to $11.86. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) rose 0.3 percent to $26.53. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
advanced 2.4 percent to $4.77. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) gained 1.7
